The paper deals with visual recognition and proposes a novel feature embedding scheme for traffic sign recognition. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also uses deep learning techniques, which makes it likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also deals with classification and recognition, which makes it possible for it to belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses a quadruplet network, which suggests that it may belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
